The paper deals with the problem of simulating interactive protocols over noisy channels, which is a classic problem in information theory (cs.IT). The focus is on Markovian protocols, which have a specific structure and are therefore likely to have specific coding techniques (cs.CC). The paper also discusses the error probability and reliability of the simulation, which are important topics in cryptography (cs.CR). The use of Markovian models is also relevant in the field of data science and machine learning (cs.DS), where they are used to model sequential data. Finally, the paper discusses the achievable rates of the coding scheme, which is a topic in information theory and communication systems (cs.SI).
